CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 3, 1951, pg. 25, reads: "Grads at Westinghouse Prom - The Tropicana Club, composed of Negro members of the February '51 class of Westinghouse High School, and their guests attended a graduation prom in the Norse Room of Fort Pitt Hotel here Friday. Officers of the club are Robert Aarons, president; Dolores Tucker, vice president; Shirley Henderson, recording secretary; Earl Lawson, treasurer; Leon Haley, corresponding secretary; Betty Coker, social chairman, and Walter Reid, financial secretary.  Mrs. Lorraine R. McCoad and Miss Catherine Henderson are sponsors."
TitMainTitle: Young men and women, possibly including Naomi Dean fourth from left, and Delphina Gray second from right, at Westinghouse High School prom, in Norse Room, Fort Pitt Hotel
